added.title: Mr. Butt
added.description: After Starfire is set up by Blackfire and sent to prison, the Titans work to make Blackfire a better sister while Starfire plots her revenge.

added.title: Man Person
added.description: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.

added.title: Pirates
added.description: When Aqualad and Raven fall for each other, Beast Boy fights this match - with intensity.

added.title: Puppets, Whaaaaat?
added.description: When Robin gets frustrated with the Titans' disobedience he turns to...puppets.

added.title: Real Magic
added.description: Robin dabbles with magic, ignoring Raven's warning that he will anger the magic god.

added.title: Creepy Crawler Creature Catcher
added.description: The hottest new game just got real. A cybervillain unleashes giant versions of the game's digital creepy crawlies across Singapore, landing the spies deep in cyber-slime. Will the spies make it through in time for Glitterstar's mysterious invitation?

added.title: Totally Vintage
added.description: When a toaster attacks Mandy, the Spies must figure out why digital smart appliances are going rogue. But when WOOHP tech turns against them, the spies discover with Toby's help that going 'vintage' could be the only way to take this villain down.

added.title: Clarence the Movie
added.description: When Clarence starts to play around with his home video camera, he becomes increasingly drawn into the world of filmmaking. From talking toys, to real actors, to documentary subjects, Clarence is determined to find the right style to tell his story!

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Brains TV
added.description: After a marathon of classic sitcom episodes, Clarence becomes stuck as alter-ego "Clarry," an obnoxiously overacting sitcom version of himself. It's up to his friends and family to help him snap out of it, or face life with a new Clarence.

added.title: Etiquette Clarence
added.description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

added.title: Video Store
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo visit their local video store to rent a movie, but discover it's all rented out! Each of them have a different idea of what tape to bring home, and must enlist the help of a tie breaker to figure it out.

added.title: Anywhere but Sumo
added.description: When Clarence realizes Sumo has made a new group of friends at his new school, he becomes jealous and confused. Will Clarence accept a school life void of Sumo, or scheme his way into making their friendship work?

added.title: Mr. McStuffles/Twinkle, Baby Looney Star (song)/Picture This!
added.description: Mr. McStuffles: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it./Picture This: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

added.title: Hair Cut-Ups/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/A Clean Sweep
added.description: Hair Cut-Ups: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut./A Clean Sweep: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

added.title: Daffy Did It!/Foghorn's Talkin' in the Barnyard (song)/Pig Who Cried Woof
added.description: Daffy Did It!: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying./The Pig Who Cried Wolf: Petunia fakes emergencies. But when a real one arises, no one believes her.

added.title: New Cat in Town/Baby Bunny (song)/The Magic of Spring
added.description: New Cat in Town: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving./The Magic of Spring: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

added.title: For Whom the Toll Calls/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Cereal Boxing
added.description: For Whom the Toll Calls: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill./Cereal Boxing: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

added.title: Barney's Big Race
added.description: Inspired by a hot-rod in Mel's dad's garage, Barney helps the kids make their own magical hot rod-style race cars! When Mel gets frustrated that she keeps losing the race, Barney helps her realize there's more to racing than just winning.

added.title: The Brave Truth
added.description: When Vivie accidentally breaks Mel's toy airplane, she's afraid to admit it. Barney creates magical knight and castle play to help Vivie feel brave enough to tell Mel the truth.

added.title: Red Light Stop, Green Light Go
added.description: Mel keeps trying to do a cool scooter trick and doesn't want to rest until she gets it right, but Mel pushes her body too far. Barney and Billy help Mel learn to listen to what her body is feeling and why it's important to do so.

added.title: Big, Bigger, Best
added.description: David feels like he's too small to do the all things his big brother can do, so Barney makes him super-sized. But throughout his super-sized adventures David realizes the importance of loving himself just as he is.

added.title: The Easter Bunnies
added.description: The Easter Bunny is sick, so she hires The Looney Builders to take over the festivities and ensure Looneyburg has a great Easter.

added.title: Junior
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Ma and Pa Bear to build a bedroom for their son, Junior, whose excitement causes setbacks.

added.title: Looney Moon
added.description: When The Looney Builders help Wile E. Coyote build a telescope to view the Looney Moon, Tweety must face his fear of the dark.

added.title: Glamp Out
added.description: Gossamer invites The Looney Builders on a camping trip. They plan to build a simple campsite until Daffy insists they go "glamping" instead.

removed.title: Mas y Menos
removed.description: Robin tries to teach his superhero ways to Spanish speaking brothers Mas y Menos.

removed.title: Dreams
removed.description: A glimpse inside each Titan's dream world.

removed.title: Missing
removed.description: Killer Moth offers a reward for Silkie's return, but will Silkier be happier away from the Titans?

removed.title: Grandma Voice
removed.description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

removed.title: Uncle Jokes
removed.description: BB and Cyborg invite Starfire to join in their fun as long as she avoids dreaded uncle jokes.

removed.title: Nose Mouth
removed.description: The Titans overuse Raven's dark magic, causing unintended consequences.

removed.title: Waffles
removed.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy annoy the other Titans by refusing to say anything but "Waffles."

removed.title: Be Mine
removed.description: Beast Boy invites Tara to the Titan's Valentine's Day dance and she accepts in order to destroy all of the Titans and exact revenge on Beast Boy.

removed.title: Breakfast Cheese
removed.description: Starfire convinces the reluctant Titans to try defeating their enemies with compassion rather than violence.
